# API

The Allegro documentation comes in the source package. Once you finish the
build process, you will end up with the documentation generated in html, rtf,
text, texinfo, chm, PostScript, PDF or devhelp file formats, depending on your
platform, installed build tools and make options. See the documentation for
makefile targets which build special formats. Here, we host some popular
versions of the generated documentation, and provide an online browseable
version too.

-------------------------------------------------------------
File format           Stable branch         Allegro 4.9
--------------------- -------------------   -----------------
Online HTML           [4.4.0][st ol]        [SVN][a5now ol] /
                                            [older][a5dir ol]

Compiled HTML         [4.2.1][st chm]
format (CHM)          (913 KiB)

PDF format            [4.2.1][st pdf]       [SVN][ext pdf]
                      (2769 KiB)

PostScript            [4.2.1][st ps]
gzipped format        (536 KiB)
--------------------------------------------------------------

[st chm]: http://prdownloads.sourceforge.net/alleg/allegro-manual-4.2.1.en.chm?download
[st ol]:  http://alleg.sourceforge.net/stabledocs/en/index.html
[st pdf]: http://prdownloads.sourceforge.net/alleg/allegro-manual-4.2.1.en.pdf?download
[st ps]:  http://prdownloads.sourceforge.net/alleg/allegro-manual-4.2.1.en.ps.gz?download

[a5now ol]:  http://alleg.sourceforge.net/a5docs/refman/index.html
[a5dir ol]:  http://alleg.sourceforge.net/a5docs/

[ext pdf]: http://www.strangesoft.net/allegro/docs/refman.pdf

[Online Documentation and Source Browser](http://srnet.cz/~stepan/allegro/) -
<br/>
The online version of the Allegro 3.12 and WIP docs, and various versions of
the sources, provided by Štěpán Roh.

[Allegro.cc's version of the manual](http://www.allegro.cc/manual/) -
<br/>
Allegro's makedoc tool is not the only way to produce documentation. Matthew
Leverton has created his own online version with a different style and URL
functionality.

Remember that apart from Allegro's excellent manual, there is also a
[tutorial](docs.html) section with links to contributed documentation.
And there are also [written paper books](books.html) which teach Allegro.
